{"showCoverPage":true,"bookCover":{"coverDescription":"<p style=\"text-align:center\">Legal and Regulatory Requirements</p>\n","coverMedium":{"params":{"decorative":true,"contentName":"Image","file":{"path":"images/image-ACN0ibuP.png","mime":"image/png","copyright":{"license":"U"},"width":1282,"height":625}},"library":"H5P.Image 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Image","license":"U","title":"Untitled Image","authors":[],"changes":[],"defaultLanguage":"en"},"subContentId":"500e04de-295e-45e8-9f3a-2f960a9d6b60"}},"chapters":[{"params":{"content":[{"content":{"params":{"text":"<p>Introduction to Legal and Regulatory Requirements:<br />\n </p>\n\n<p>The trucking industry is heavily regulated, and it is crucial for entrepreneurs to understand the legal and regulatory requirements that they must comply with. This section will provide an overview of the different types of regulations that apply to the trucking industry.</p>\n"},"library":"H5P.AdvancedText 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"Introduction to Legal and Regulatory Requirements:","authors":[],"changes":[]},"subContentId":"e6d7d3ce-b936-458c-be2b-6fc37ea2be2e"},"useSeparator":"auto"}]},"library":"H5P.Column 1.16","subContentId":"3f3e0a76-fa41-4d57-8121-b14f14444883","metadata":{"contentType":"Column","license":"U","title":"Introduction","authors":[],"changes":[],"extraTitle":"Introduction"}},{"params":{"content":[{"content":{"params":{"text":"<p>FMCSA Regulations:<br />\n </p>\n\n<p>The Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration (FMCSA) is the primary regulatory body governing the trucking industry in the United States. This section will discuss the various FMCSA regulations, including those related to driver qualifications, hours of service, vehicle maintenance, and commercial driver’s license requirements.</p>\n"},"library":"H5P.AdvancedText 1.1","metadata":{"contentType":"Text","license":"U","title":"FMCSA Regulations:","authors":[],"changes":[]},"subContentId":"e04f4ed5-d60c-43a1-b8a2